Ahh the fabled "Woodruff key" - what is it ? All the books mention it
without saying what it looks like and how you unlock(pun intended) it.

It may be that the alternator needs re-building (read chucking away and
replacing) but since it is still generating the requisite amount of
electricity and is otherwise fine I hope not. The squeaky noise coming from
it is worse on hot days or if I spray WD40 behind the pulley so I suspect
the front bearing just needs proper lubrication. Whatever it needs though,
that pulley has to come off !

