The rear part of the pulley is on a taper I believe, plus which there's a
woodruff key in there. You could spray some penetrating oil in there from
both sides, wait for it to work it's way in. You will need to pry that rear
half off with long pry bars or screwdrivers. It should come off fairly
easily.
Alternator bearing needs grease? Are you sure it doesn't need a rebuild?
I've never heard of greasing alternators.
Tom

